$interpreted: Calm Alliance Soldier: ...Everything has been done according your instructions, my liege.
Toyokuni: Very well. If you should find any victims while patrolling the vicinity, take them to safety and don't allow them to interfere with the tests.
Calm Alliance Soldier: Yes, sir!
Toyokuni: I only hope the tests go well, and that the trap will work on the Monster of Judgment...
Alliance Soldier: My lord! We've brought you a despicable worm!
Tindoiimu: Guh... Toyo... kuni...?
Tindoiimu: Toyokuni! What's happened to the circus that I was with!? You have to let them go, they're innocent!
Toyokuni: Calm yourself. You'll only make more trouble for yourself like that.
Toyokuni: Leave us, I have questions to ask of her.
Toyokuni: I never imagined that our next meeting would happen like this...
Toyokuni: ...Anyway, let us talk.
Tindoiimu: ...What's to talk about, with things as they are now? It's just as you said, I've brought catastrophe upon the East.
Tindoiimu: I don't care... but don't drag Sophie and the rest into this.
Toyokuni: Are you not even willing to defend yourself?
Tindoiimu: What's the use? I'm just an Insect, up against Juan-Yun's accusations. Who would you believe, if you were a common Easterner?
Toyokuni: ...I, at least, don't think it was you.
Toyokuni: Destroying Udumbara, awakening the Monster of Judgment... You'd have enough of a motive, indeed, but... I just can't believe you capable of it.
Tindoiimu: Toyokuni...
Tindoiimu: ...Actually, I—
Toyokuni: Not to mention your relationship with Juan-Yun... You'd never seek to kill him, and he... He cares for you. He has no reason to make false accusations.
Toyokuni: The contradictions leave me clueless... I must speak with you privately about it.
Tindoiimu: ...Juan-Yun... cares for me...?
Toyokuni: Anybody can see that. He'd just rather not face up to it.
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...Haha...
Tindoiimu: Yeah, I once thought I could see it, too. But I was blind.
Toyokuni: What do you mean? You—
Tindoiimu: ...Let's not get into that, Toyokuni. It's pointless. You're an honest person, and I don't want to implicate you any further.
Toyokuni: But you do know that Juan-Yun... has agreed to go with us to fight the Monster of Judgment?
Tindoiimu: How could he...?
Toyokuni: It's a battle from which he may never return. You shouldn't do anything that might be a cause for regrets...
Tindoiimu: Toyokuni! It can't be true, he mustn't go!
Toyokuni: Can't it? What's got you riled up all of a sudden?
Tindoiimu: (Even if this has all been Juan-Yun's doing, I still don't have any proof...)
Panicked Alliance Soldier: We've got a problem! Toyokuni, sir!
Panicked Alliance Soldier: It's the Insects! The Insects are coming!
Toyokuni: Impossible! How'd they get past our defences!?
Panicked Alliance Soldier: My subordinates aren't sure either, they just suddenly ambushed us!
Toyokuni: Quickly, get to the Tiger Tribe patrol on the west side and call them in for support!
Tindoiimu: Wait, Toyokuni!
Toyokuni: I'm sorry, Tindoiimu. We'll talk later.
Toyokuni: You, stay here and watch over the Insect Princess. Everyone else, come with me!
Tindoiimu: (The Insects... at a time like this... Who could it be?)
Insect Vanguard: Push!! Fellow tribespeople, today we slaughter each and every one of these foul beasts!
Stunned Alliance Soldier: En... Enemies! C-counter them! Stop those Insects in their tracks!
Jihasaha: Come on, they're here. What are you waiting for?
Jihasaha: Vanguards, listen up! Take them all out before they rebuild their defences—CHAAARGE!
